A decent game but very inaccurate in some parts. For example I've done the research and privateers working for a country at war did not keep their notoriety with that country's enemies once the war was over. I find that very frustrating as I have been sunk or caught and hung trying to pay off my notoriety after a war is over quite a bit. Plus privateers were officially sanctioned so they wouldn't have been put to death on the charge of piracy. In other words, pirates were criminals, privateers were not. Also the in game currency doesn't come at a quick enough income rate so I end up broke way more often than necessary. It'd be nice if players could either customize their own unique flag at the beginning, or if there was atleast a wider selection of flags to choose from. Other than that it's an ok game.

content: Outstanding.  The demo let's you have a taste and see if it's for you, then you get the option to pay for the full version with ZERO ads or any intrusions. I feel this is how it should be and I applaud the developers for that choice.   The game can seem daunting at first but it is very satisfying to claw your way to the top so I urge you to stick with it.   The majority of game mechanics work well and the stories are interesting and fun to pursue. Very few bugs and no crashes (HTC one M8) so far.   If you liked Sid Meiers Pirates! then you should get this game as it is very similar.   ---------------------------------  I wish you could have a fleet of ships instead of being confined to one ship as the enemy garrisons are so huge in the late game that towns become unassailable. I had a ship with 450 elite sailors (modifications left me with 16 cargo slots) and we just scraped a victory against 600 Spaniards. (Apprentice diff)   It does get repetitive and it may feel like a grind at times, I can imagine that people may be put off by it but you need to build your infrastructure beforehand, it's all the more rewarding.   I'd like to see interactions with governers deepened and maybe the option to go freelance and maybe include a pirate faction.   Fantastic game, will be even better with future updates.

This is a game set in the 17th century Caribbean with you as a swashbuckling captain of a ship.  As the title suggests, you will come across many other characters, mainly pirates and traders.  Being a pirate or a trader are also the main routes that you can take to making your fortune.    Pirates and traders offers you tons of options.  First of all, there is an in depth character creation process where you choose your nationality, your traits and your ship.  Once you are on the  high seas, you can search them for other ships to plunder either solely for treasure or in the name of your country or you can sail from port to port looking for deals on the many commodities sold and keeping an ear out for any rumours of surpluses or shortages so that you can buy low and sell high.  The game does not stop there, however.  You can also take part in missions such as pirate hunting, delivering items or tryiong to smuggle contraband into certain ports.  There are also other story modules coming up.  There is always something to aim for.  You can upgrade your personal equipment and ship until you have a mighty floating fortress crewed by an elite army of sailors.  Great graphics  and music too
